15: You don't even know what's wrong!
18:
So I don't! But I do know that
something troubles you, Alk. I shall
clear it up forthwith!
21:
Oh, uh, thanks... Okay, so the problem
is, the Guild wants us to take down
this monster, but it's pretty far.
23:
I'm talking days of trekking in the
wilderness before we get there.
But all of our fighters who are used to
roughing it are busy right now.
26:
A battle against a dastardly beast, 
you say?
Ahh... Even now, I can hear the cries of 
distress... Like cacophonous music to 
my ears...
28:
Very well! I shall join the quest to fell
this vile creature! Consider your
worries over, Alk!
31:
You're gonna march the whole 
distance in that armor?
Oh, wait, no... You must have a horse!
34:
Knights ride horses! Duh. It's how you
all go on those long campaigns, right?
40: I'd, er... prefer NOT to go by horse...
43:
Why not? It's a heck of a lot faster
than going by foot.
48:
I-I... Well, er... But... But what about
you?! You would arrive days after me!
52:
No, no. We go by carriage. No one
charges ahead, and no one gets left
behind. It's perfect. Yes. We simply
MUST go by carriage!
55:
Yeah, I guess you have a point...
All right, Gerard! By carriage it is, then!
58:
Splendid! Fear not, helpless citizens,
for help is coming!
63:
Kind sirs! Thank you greatly for comin'
out to our humble little village!
66:
Sure... No problem. We climbed over
two mountains to get here, but... Who
doesn't love a good hike?
69:
You have a lovely village, good sir.
The vegetables in the field are thriving.
Products of rich soil, no doubt!
71:
Got an eye for soil, do you, Sir Knight?
Yes, our lovely dirt is the pride and joy
of our village!
72:
But don't listen to me, ramblin' on
about filth. You'll be wantin' to know
what the mission is. See, there's been
a great big boar about who's been
wreckin' our fields!
74:
So we're here to defeat a boar then,
and not a monster.
79:
No, my good champion. You must not
speak lightly of the boar. It is a foul
and vicious beast!
81:
It feeds upon all that lies or stands
beneath the sun. It can devour all
a village's fields in a day, or
a mountain's roots, leaves, and
shrooms overnight!
84:
With its snout, it can raze the paddies
and fields, filling in ditches that do
bring water to the vegetables, or
trampling tender sprouts with
its hooves.
88:
Boars are a scourge!
A pestilence that must be cured!
92: You, uh... sure have me convinced.
99:
So you're acceptin' the quest, then?
Perfect! Now let me lead you to where
the rotter's been—
101: I-It's back! The boar's come back!
109:
Yes. Worry not, old man! A boar or two
is no match for—
123: Careful! That is no mere animal!
127:
Calm yourself, my good champion.
I have faced boars of this girth in
battle before.
128:
Boars are ravaging whirlwinds of
destruction. However, I must say...
136:
Their meat is most delicious! Boar
stew is on the menu tonight,
my good sirs!
147:
Victory is mine! Now what say we
bring the creature home, flush out its
blood, and have ourselves a feast?
163:
You know much about boars, and
the havoc they wreak.  Are you from
a farming village yourself?
169:
Su-surely you must be jesting!
I'm a knight, through and through!
I was raised in a great house, in an
even greater city!
171:
Now, come! We mustn't tarry any
longer! The good citizens of Starview
Village are waiting for us!
180:
Huh? I mean, yeah. He's always
been strange.
184:
Yes, but... Perhaps I said something
I shouldn't have.
187:
Gerard! Hold up! Home's in the
opposite direction!
